lfonso, Amador, Andres, Aniceto, Delfino, Emilio.","Spanish (<b>Crespín</b>): variant of   Crispin  .","French: from the Latin personal name <i>Crispinus</i> (see   Crispin  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Crispin","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Juan, Pedro, Alicia, Fernando, Manuel, Rafael, Adolfo, Alfredo, Ana, Areli, Candita.  French Adrien, Andre, Eugenie, Francoise.","English; Spanish (<b>Crispín</b>): from the personal name Middle English <i>Crispin</i>, Spanish <i>Crispín</i>, from Latin <i>Crispinus</i>, derived from <i>crispus</i> ‘curly-haired’ (see   Crisp  ). This name was especially popular in France in the early Middle Ages, having been borne by a Christian saint who was martyred at Soissons in  AD <i>c.</i> 285 along with a companion, <i>Crispinianus</i> (whose name is a further derivative of the same word). Compare   Crespin   and 3 below.","English (of Norman origin): from Old French and Middle English <i>crespin</i>, <i>crispin</i> ‘curly-haired’, also found as <i>Crepin</i>; see   Crippin  . It is difficult to tell this apart from the personal name in 1 above. According to Lanfranc, archbishop of Canterbury (1070–1089), the Norman Gilbert Crispin was the first man to receive this nickname, and two of his sons adopted it as their surname. His grandson Gilbert Crispin became abbot of Westminster in 1085. Members of the Norman family were said to have inherited a shock of hair that stood up stiffly like a bristly pine, as though the name derived from Latin <i>crispus pinus</i>, but this derivation is a medieval invention."]}]},{"name":"Joscelin","type":"FIRST","meanings":["A female name, found written Joscelyne and Jocelin, and by corruption Joscelind. A diminutive formed from Latin Justus. The German name Jost is rendered Joscelin."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Joscelin Crespin was born about 1125, in Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, his father, Gullaume III Crespin, was 32 and his mother, Yvonne de Tancarville, was 26. He married Isabelle du Plessis Dame de Dangu in 1141, in Crespin, Aveyron, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1193, at the age of 70."},"et":{"about 1125–about 1193":"umbes 1125–umbes 1193","1125–1193":"1125–1193","1125–Female":"1125–Surnud","1143–1223":"1143–1223","1095–1135":"1095–1135","1100–Female":"1100–Surnud","about 1193":"umbes 1193","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","1223":"1223","1100":"1100","about 1125":"umbes 1125","1143":"1143","1141":"1141","about 1135":"umbes 1135","1095":"1095","1193":"1193","Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Crespin, Aveyron, France":"Crespin, Aveyron, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1125–about 1193":"noin 1125–noin 1193","1125–1193":"1125–1193","1125–Female":"1125–Kuollut","1143–1223":"1143–1223","1095–1135":"1095–1135","1100–Female":"1100–Kuollut","about 1193":"noin 1193","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","1223":"1223","1100":"1100","about 1125":"noin 1125","1143":"1143","1141":"1141","about 1135":"noin 1135","1095":"1095","1193":"1193","Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Ranska","Crespin, Aveyron, France":"Crespin, Aveyron, Ranska","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"about 1125–about 1193":"environ 1125–environ 1193","1125–1193":"1125–1193","1125–Female":"1125–Décédée","1143–1223":"1143–1223","1095–1135":"1095–1135","1100–Female":"1100–Décédée","about 1193":"environ 1193","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","1223":"1223","1100":"1100","about 1125":"environ 1125","1143":"1143","1141":"1141","about 1135":"environ 1135","1095":"1095","1193":"1193","Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","Crespin, Aveyron, France":"Crespin, Aveyron, France","France":"France","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Joscelin Crespin est né environ 1125, à Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, son père, Gullaume III Crespin, avait 32 ans et sa mère, Yvonne de Tancarville, avait 26 ans. Il a épousé Isabelle du Plessis Dame de Dangu en 1141, à Crespin, Aveyron, 